text: Abortions
label: BODY

text: In accordance with federal law, abortions are covered only (1) if the
label: BODY

text: pregnancy is the result of an act of rape or incest; or (2) where a woman
label: BODY

text: suffers from a physical disorder, physical injury, or physical illness,
label: BODY

text: including a life-endangering physical condition caused by or arising from
label: BODY

text: the pregnancy itself, that would, as certified by a physician, place the
label: BODY

text: woman in danger of death unless an abortion is performed.
label: BODY

text: Please refer to Appendix E, Medicaid Forms, for a copy of the PHY-96-2
label: BODY

text: Certification and Documentation for Abortion form, which is used when the
label: BODY

text: pregnancy is causing the life of the mother to be in danger. In the case of
label: BODY

text: abortions performed secondary to pregnancies resulting from rape or
label: BODY

text: incest, the documentation required is a letter from the recipient or provider
label: BODY

text: certifying that the pregnancy resulted from rape or incest.
label: BODY

text: The original copy of the PHY-96-2 form (for life of the mother in
label: BODY

text: danger) signed by the attending physician, or the certification letter
label: BODY

text: regarding rape or incest, and a copy of the medical records (history
label: BODY

text: and physical, operative report and discharge summary) must be
label: BODY

text: submitted to EDS.
label: BODY

text: The second copy of the consent form or certification letter must be
label: BODY

text: placed in the recipient’s medical record.
label: BODY

text: Copies of the consent form or certification letter may need to be
label: BODY

text: provided to hospital, laboratory or other providers as applicable in
label: BODY

text: order for them to submit billing for their services.
label: BODY

text: All claims relating to abortions must have the above-specified
label: BODY

text: documentation on file at EDS prior to payment.
label: BODY

text: This documentation is not required when a recipient presents with a
label: BODY

text: spontaneous abortion.
label: BODY

text: If the recipient does not qualify for payment by Medicaid and elects to have the
label: BODY

text: abortion, providers may bill the recipient for the abortion as a non-covered

text: service.
